name: minimalist style - makise kurisu
description:
I'll try to update again in June, as I ran out of Colab credits and wanted to take some time off.

The current model is in the experimental stage (I am learning how to train the Lora model).

Probably v0.3.0 is the best version. This needs to be chosen according to your personal preference.

If you think this Lora model is not very bad, then thank you very much.

If you like this Lora model, you may consider clicking the like button.

I would recommend mixing multiple Lora versions. At the moment I can not make a very good Lora model.

class_tokens = "makise kurisu 1girl"

If you want to generate details such as makise kurisu outfit and pupil color, I prefer to use: ultra detailed, 1girl, makise kurisu, slim, tall, auburn hair, soft curls, green eyes, labcoat, red tie, professional, serious, black shorts, black socks, brown loafers, sleek, sophisticated, stylish, <lora:makise kurisu:0.6>,

modelVersions.name: v0.4.5(test2) CLAHE Color
modelVersions.description: This version does not generate very good details, because I spent very little time training this version (only a test version, I will try some new things, so the generated images do not always look good). You will see some details blurred or missing in this version, because I used too high denoise to process the image (sorry). I don't know what you guys think of this version, but I think it's barely good enough for 1900 steps.

modelVersions.description:
• The v0.4.0 version uses a mask to divide the foreground and background, which I think has some effect; when you set too high a weight, like <lora:makise kurisu:0.8>, you'll see a translucent mask between the hair gaps.Unless you set a suitable weight, such as <lora:makise kurisu:0.6>.

  • I'm sorry if you see the hand details are terrible.I don't know how to fix the detailed performance of the extremities.I don't want a lot of training steps at the moment to address the concept of fingers and toes.If you have prepared some means of fixing it yourself, that's great.

modelVersions.name: v0.3.5 abandoned
modelVersions.description:
• v0.3.5 is currently a final version, but I think it is not the best.

  • Probably v0.3.0 is the best version. This needs to be chosen according to your personal preference.

  1. tried to increase the number of training steps.

    1. but this has little effect.

  2. tried to use self-defining texture background, and in general some unnecessary parts will be learned.

    1. Need to be used with caution, unless the Lora model has a fixed constant scene as background, it is better to use a solid color background.

  3. the use of translucent mask to divide the foreground and background areas, this practice has advantages and disadvantages.

    1. to a certain extent, to limit the subject's identification area. But the shortcomings will slightly affect the color of the subject.
